<p dir="ltr">&lt;Job position : Global Community Manager&gt;</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p dir="ltr">Location - Seocho-gu, Seoul</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p dir="ltr">The Global Community Managers will play a key role to build and expand community, and are responsible to define, deliver and maintain users&#39;s interest and attention with constant interaction with the communities.</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p dir="ltr">Duties and Responsibilities</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p dir="ltr">- Manage and expand communities</p>

<p dir="ltr">- Research use cases and educate users</p>

<p dir="ltr">- Communicate with different users groups</p>

<p dir="ltr">- Provide analysis and insights to improve user&rsquo;s experience</p>

<p dir="ltr">- Monitor performance of the service and content value</p>

<p><br />
&nbsp;</p>

<p dir="ltr">Skills and Specifications</p>

<p dir="ltr">- Must have excellent communication skills both written and verbal at least within one of the following languages: English / Chinese(Mandarin)</p>

<p dir="ltr">- Must be able to communicate in either English or Korean</p>

<p dir="ltr">- Interest in pop culture and entertainment media. (Hollywood, K-POP, J-POP etc.)</p>

<p dir="ltr">- Must have logical and expressive writing skill</p>

<p dir="ltr">- Must be Internet and tech savvy</p>

<p dir="ltr">- Able to use or is using any SNS (Facebook, Blog, Twitter) or any other online media service</p>

<p><br />
&nbsp;</p>

<p dir="ltr">Preferential Qualification</p>

<p dir="ltr">- Experience in operating blog or any community service (forums, groups)</p>

<p dir="ltr">- Enough experience of residence in applying language&rsquo;s country</p>

<p dir="ltr">- Deep understanding in Fandom or has experience at fan group</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p dir="ltr">Terms and Requirements</p>

<p dir="ltr">- Must be eligible to work at least 6 month in South Korea</p>

<p dir="ltr">- Begin as full-time contractor. Future promotions may take place according to performance.</p>

